<taxonomicName authority="Asakawa et al. 2017" authorityName="Asakawa" authorityYear="2017" box="[232,656,339,363]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[232,441,339,363]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829">Lactobacillus curtus</emphasis>
Asakawa 
<emphasis box="[547,591,339,363]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</taxonomicName>
, 3905 
<superScript attach="right" box="[718,738,338,352]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829">VP</superScript>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[120,760,184,685]" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829">
It grows over a wide pH range (pH 3.5–8.5) and at 15 °C but not at 45 °C [
<bibRefCitation author="Asakawa Y &amp; Takesue N &amp; Asano S &amp; Shimotsu S &amp; Iijima K" box="[260,306,416,440]" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829" pagination="3899 - 3906" refId="ref70573" refString="244. Asakawa Y, Takesue N, Asano S, Shimotsu S, Iijima K et al. Lactobacillus curtus sp. nov., isolated from beer in Finland. Int J Syst Evol Microbiol 2017; 67: 3899 - 3906." type="journal article" year="2017">244</bibRefCitation>
]. The mol% G+C content of DNA is 43.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[120,760,184,685]" box="[121,404,461,485]" pageId="47" pageNumber="2829">Isolated from spoiled beer.</paragraph>
